Title: ForcePianoFingering
JsName: forcePianoFingering
DataAttribute: data-force-piano-fingering
Category: Core
Description: Forces the fingering rendering to use always the piano finger style.
ShowInSideBar: false
---

<h2>Description</h2>
<p>
    The fingering information for piano is annotated as 1-5 for the individual fingers. For some other instruments like guitars it usually is rendered as p,i,m,a,c and T,1,2,3,4 depending on the hand. 
    This setting allows enforcing of the piano fingering for all instruments. 
</p>

<h2>Types</h2>

<table class="table table-striped table-condensed type-table">
    <tbody>    
        <tr>
            <td><code>bool</td>
        </tr>   
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Default Value</h2>

<code>false<code>

<h2>Example - C#</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-csharp line-numbers">
var settings = Settings.Defaults; 
settings.ForcePianoFingering = true;
</code>
</pre>


<h2>Example - JavaScript</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-javascript line-numbers">
var settings = {
    forcePianoFingering: 'true'
};
var api = new alphaTab.platform.javaScript.AlphaTabApi(document.querySelector('#alphaTab'), settings);
var japi = $('#alphaTab').alphaTab(settings);
</code>
</pre>

<h2>Example - HTML</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-html line-numbers">
&lt;div id="alphaTab" data-force-piano-fingering="true"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</code>
</pre>